parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can cause accidents or injuries due to reduced visibility while reversing.
symptoms: The backup camera is not available
the screen is badly distorted
cuts in and out
or the image looks like a ghost.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The door ajar issue can cause wind noise, water, insects, and other hazards to enter the cabin of the vehicle, while the window issue can lead to water and debris entering the vehicle.
symptoms: The passenger door becomes unlatched while driving
the door doesn't fully open
the "DOOR AJAR" display goes off with audible alarms
the passenger window's auto/short drop feature isn't working
and the window does not go back up fully.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel can cause the loss of critical information, such as speed and engine performance, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The instrument panel goes blank
the digital dash goes dark
or the LCD dashboard fails to light up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of issues, including loss of power, stalling, and failure of critical systems, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the brakes lock up
the headlights flash
the car will not lock or unlock
and the hood or trunk will not open.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window motor can cause the window to malfunction, allowing water, insects, and other hazards to enter the cabin of the vehicle.
symptoms: The passenger power window rolls down without any buttons being pushed
and the window will not stay up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, lurch, or hesitate while shifting, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission shifts harshly
hesitates
or lurches while shifting
the vehicle jerks or bangs while braking
the transmission makes a clunking or grinding noise
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into gear
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle experiences sudden acceleration or deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Train Malfunction (Clutch and Flywheel Failure)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and flywheel can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or experience difficulty shifting, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle experiences difficulty shifting into gear
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the clutch makes a grinding or screeching noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Instrument Panel and Accessories)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the instrument panel to malfunction, leading to loss of critical information, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The instrument panel blacked out
the vehicle's electrical systems failed to operate
the rear-view camera was inoperable
the gear indicator failed to display on the instrument panel
the rev-matching feature was inoperable while downshifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driveshaft can cause the vehicle to experience misfiring, knocking sounds, and fumes, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: The vehicle experienced misfiring
a knocking sound was coming from underneath the vehicle while shifting into reverse
fumes were coming from outside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the differential coolant line can cause the vehicle to experience leaks, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: A leak was discovered underneath the vehicle
the differential coolant line needed to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Coolant intrusion into engine cylinders can cause engine misfires, loss of power, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Check engine light illumination
misfires
loss of power
engine shaking or stuttering
coolant leak into cylinders
engine replacement required.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil pressure switch failure can cause inaccurate oil pressure readings, leading to engine damage or failure, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Oil pressure gauge shows incorrect readings
engine light illumination
faulty oil pressure switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling or lunging can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling or lunging
jerking or hesitation when accelerating
check engine light illumination.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Valve or Rocker Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure due to valve or rocker issues can cause sudden engine failure, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Metallic grinding noises
engine lock-up
sudden loss of power
engine replacement required.
